description.narrative: The long-term development objective of the Land Administration Project is to improve the security of land tenure and thereby: (i) develop and establish a national policy, legal, institutional and technical framework to support a systematic property rights administration that is efficient, reliable and equitable; (ii) develop, implement and validate a systematic methodology, which would accelerate and improve the processing of requests for new titles and title reviews in three departments so that it could be subsequently applied nationwide; eliminate backlog of title requests; (iii) achieve substantial progress in the recognition and definition of Indigenous Peoples land rights and demarcate 15 territories and community lands; (iv) achieve substantial progress in the definition and demarcation of existing and proposed protected areas and critical habitats.

condition.narrative: General directorate of land and agrarian reform within MAGFOR.
Operational Manual, Project Implementation Plan, and Subproyect Operational Manual
Submit to National Assembly a Cadastre Law.

title.narrative: Organizational Development Plans designed, approved, and implemented.
At least 40% of new titles are provided directly to women and/or jointly with their spouse/partner.

comment.narrative: An estimate based on the draft evaluation report. Final figure to be confirmed.

title.narrative: Diagnostics to identify land tenure status on ejido and municipal lands have been carried out in at least 33 municipalities, to support titling processes.

comment.narrative: There are 22 diagnostics on land tenure status by INIFOM.

title.narrative: Cadastral surveying database transferred to at least 33 municipalities in the pilot area; and in 4 municipalities SIICAR and SISCATshare data as well as resources and technology for their management.
At least 70 % of beneficiaries receiving new rural titles fall under the category of "very small producer".

comment.narrative: An estimate based on the draft evaluation report. Final figure to be confirmed.

title.narrative: Land taxation rates updated in 33 municipalities in the pilot area through the use of cadastral survey information in SISCAT.

comment.narrative: Databases transfered to 30 municipalities including information of over 300,000 parcels. Final figure to be confirmed.

title.narrative: SIIPRO contains updated information of the regularization cases submitted to the IP central level.
Key legal and procedural reforms have been approved, that permit to carry out massive national regularization program by the end ofthe project.

comment.narrative: No Indigenous Land Titling Law; Registry Law did not allow SIICAR; legal difficulties for regularization.
The Project supported the approval of: Law for Titling of Indigenous Peoples' Lands (2002); Cadastre Law (2004); andPublicRegistryLaw (2009)

title.narrative: At least 50% reduction in number of days required to register a transaction in SIICAR, in the pilot area.

comment.narrative: No system existed at the moment of Project appraisal
SIICAR has been made operational recently in Chinandega. In all other areas there is a reduction of at least 50% in the number ofdays required to register a transaction. Final figure to be confirmed.

title.narrative: All protected areas under the Project are included in INETER's geographical database.

comment.narrative: PAs were not demarcated or geo-referenced

title.narrative: Indigenous Peoples' rights are enforced in 15 territories and respected by government authorities, and the national regional and municipal levels.

comment.narrative: Territories were not demarcated or titled
Activities completed under the original Credit.

title.narrative: At least 52,282 rural and urban parcels regularized in the pilot area.

comment.narrative: Measurement corrected. 62.5% actually achieved thus far.32,677parcels regularized: 20,197 rural titles; 12,480 urban titles.

title.narrative: At least 4,985 cases resolved by OCI, along with the provision of compensation resolutions.
At least 12,600 of regularized parcels in the pilot area receive new titles.

comment.narrative: Target surpassed (255%). 32,677 titles; 20,197 rural and 12,480 urban.

title.narrative: At least 14,230 pending urban titles resolved.
At least 40% of the territory under irregular land tenure status (i.e. reformed sector, national and state land) in the pilot area has legal certainty about tenure.

baseline.value: 0 % of the pilot area was regularized

comment.narrative: Based on preliminary findings from ongoing final project evaluation. Final figure to be confirmed.

title.narrative: Land policy framework prepared and consulted with key land administration actors.

baseline.value: Land Policy framewoek document did not exist

target.value: Land Policy Framework Document endorsed and in use.

comment.narrative: Policy Framework advanced through a consultation process.

title.narrative: At least 2,225 detected boundary conflicts mediated.

comment.narrative: Out of 2,667 cases, 1,622 have been mediated. Out of these, 912 have reached an agreement.

title.narrative: SIICAR linking the legal and geographic information on each property is fully operational in 4 pilot departments.

comment.narrative: SIICAR is operational in Chinandega. Estelí 12% of progress, León and Madriz have 6% of progress.
Target achieved under the original Credit.

title.narrative: At least 14 protected areas under the Project demarcated.
At least 7 management plans prepared and implemented.

comment.narrative: Target surpassed in the case of preparation of management plans.

title.narrative: At least 5 of titled territories have a productive subproject under implementation.
At least 80% of regular properties included in SIICAR CAT are transferred to SIICAR REG.

comment.narrative: Measurement corrected. 10,990 properties transfered thus far.

title.narrative: INETER has opened departmental offices where lacking in the Project area.

comment.narrative: INETER offices operating in Project area, including Madriz.

title.narrative: UTOs established and maintaining close coordination in municipalities where surveying has been completed.

baseline.value: UTOs did not exist before the Project

comment.narrative: Three UTOs integrated into regional offices of relevant agencies under the AF (in Chinandega, Esteli and Madriz).

title.narrative: At least 30% reduction in the average number of days to regularize property rights through the Property Intendancy in the pilot area.

comment.narrative: Figure based on preliminary findings from ongoing final project evaluation. Data analysis is currently being finalized and it willbe included in the ICR.

title.narrative: Public Registries in the pilot area are financially sustainable.

comment.narrative: The evaluation report confirmed that the Public Registries in the pilot area are financially sustainable. The final data analysisis being conducted as part of the final evaluation report.
